{"type":"message","id":"4821ecb2","parentId":"ca27c6c6","timestamp":"2026-03-07T02:31:49.615Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the issue clearly. The `memory_search` tool in OpenClaw failed because it was trying to use a collection named `memory-dir-main-2` which doesn't exist. The actual QMD collections are named `workspace` and `memory`. The search itself works fine when called directly via `qmd search`.\n\nLet me explain this clearly to the user.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Here's the full breakdown:\n\n## Why memory_search Failed\n\nThe error was explicit:\n```\nCollection not found: memory-dir-main-2\n```\n\nOpenClaw's `memory_search` tool was looking for a QMD collection named **`memory-dir-main-2`**, but your actual QMD collections are named **`workspace`** and **`memory`**. Name mismatch = empty results. The data was always there — `qmd search \"pink elephant\"` finds it just fine right now.\n\n---\n\n## How to Fix It\n\n**Option 1 — OpenClaw config (preferred)**\nCheck your OpenClaw config for a `memory.collectionName` or similar setting and make sure it matches what `qmd collection list` shows. It should be `memory`, not `memory-dir-main-2`.\n\n**Option 2 — Rename the QMD collection** to match what OpenClaw expects:\n```bash\nqmd collection rename memory memory-dir-main-2\n```\n(But I'd fix the config instead — renaming the collection is fragile.)\n\n---\n\n## Making Search Faster & More Efficient\n\nA few issues I spotted from `qmd status`:\n\n1. **No GPU** — models are running on CPU with only 2 math cores. Embeddings and reranking are slow. If your Mac has Metal support, enable it when building/installing QMD.\n\n2. **Re-index regularly** — run `qmd update` after sessions so new memory files get indexed. Right now it was 2h stale.\n\n3. **Run `qmd embed`** — this pre-generates vector embeddings so `vsearch` and `query` work fast at search time instead of computing on-demand.\n\n4. **Duplicate collections** — `workspace` and `memory` both seem to index overlapping files (your memory files appear in both). Worth cleaning that up so results aren't duplicated.\n\nWant me to dig into the OpenClaw config to find the collection name mismatch and fix it?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":566,"cacheRead":17721,"cacheWrite":1257,"totalTokens":19545,"cost":{"input":0.000003,"output":0.008490000000000001,"cacheRead":0.0053162999999999995,"cacheWrite":0.00471375,"total":0.01852305}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772850694832}}
