{"type":"message","id":"c2766cce","parentId":"0723b916","timestamp":"2026-03-07T02:38:01.241Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found it! The key function is `resolveCustomPaths`:\n\n```js\nconst name = ensureUniqueName(scopeCollectionBase(entry.name?.trim() || `custom-${index + 1}`, agentId), existing);\n```\n\nSo it:\n1. Takes the entry name (`workspace` or `memory-dir`)\n2. Calls `scopeCollectionBase(name, agentId)` → produces `workspace-main` or `memory-dir-main`\n3. Calls `ensureUniqueName(name, existing)` → if the name already exists in `existing`, appends `-2`, `-3`, etc.\n\n\n4. The `existing` set comes from default memory collections that are processed first, so I need to trace through `resolveDefaultMemoryCollections` to see what names are already reserved before custom paths get their turn.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Found the culprit. Let me look at `ensureUniqueName` and `resolveDefaultMemoryCollections`:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_01TK5zwwcALXYC9B6WFWDBf5","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"node -e \"\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst src = fs.readFileSync('/usr/local/Cellar/node@22/22.22.0_1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/memory-cli-Dbqd9zVu.js', 'utf8');\n\n// Find ensureUniqueName\nlet idx = src.indexOf('function ensureUniqueName');\nif (idx === -1) idx = src.indexOf('ensureUniqueName =');\nconsole.log('=== ensureUniqueName ===');\nconsole.log(src.slice(idx, idx+400));\n\n// Find resolveDefaultMemoryCollections\nidx = src.indexOf('resolveDefaultMemoryCollections');\nconsole.log('\\n=== resolveDefaultMemoryCollections ===');\nconsole.log(src.slice(idx, idx+800));\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":514,"cacheRead":42018,"cacheWrite":519,"totalTokens":43052,"cost":{"input":0.000003,"output":0.00771,"cacheRead":0.0126054,"cacheWrite":0.00194625,"total":0.02226465}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":17728510