{"type":"message","id":"4d3687f3","parentId":"4fb28351","timestamp":"2026-03-07T02:39:25.300Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture:\n\n**Default collections** (always created when `includeDefaultMemory: true`):\n1. `memory-root-main` → workspace/MEMORY.md\n2. `memory-alt-main` → workspace/memory.md\n3. `memory-dir-main` → workspace/memory/**/*.md\n\n**Custom paths** (from openclaw.json `paths` array):\n1. `workspace-main` → workspace/**/*.md (name: \"workspace\")\n2. `memory-dir-main-2` → workspace/memory/**/*.md (name: \"memory-dir\")\n\nWait! The custom path named \"memory-dir\" after scoping becomes `memory-dir-main`, but `memory-dir-main` is already in the `nameSet` (from the default collections)! So `ensureUniqueName` returns `memory-dir-main-2` instead!\n\n\nThat's the root cause—the user configured a custom path with `name: \"memory-dir\"` that collides with the default collection's base name, causing it to get renamed to `memory-dir-main-2`. But the QMD index only knows about `memory-dir-main` from the defaults, so there's a mismatch. The solution is to rename that custom path in openclaw.json to avoid conflicting with the reserved default names like `memory-root`, `memory-alt`, and `memory-dir`.\n\nLooking at the actual configuration, the second custom path pointing to `workspace/memory` is redundant since the defaults already cover that directory. I should either remove it entirely or rename it to something like `session-logs` or `daily-notes` to avoid the collision. The first custom path for `workspace` doesn't conflict with default names, though it does overlap with what the default memory collections already index. supposed to be `memory-dir`) → workspace/memory/**/*.md\n\nThey're the SAME path/pattern! So the custom path is completely redundant with the default. The fix is to just remove the `memory-dir` custom path.\n\nAnd the `workspace` custom path covers workspace/**/*.md, which includes MEMORY.md, memory.md, and the memory/ dir. This overlaps with all defaults but isn't a naming conflict (different base name).\n\nSo the optimal fix:\n1. Remove the redundant `memory-dir` entry from custom paths (it's covered by defaults)\n2. OR rename it to something non-conflicting\n\nAnd since the default `memory-dir-main` already covers memory/**/*.md, removing the custom `memory-dir` path is the cleanest fix.\n\nBut the broader `workspace` collection would also capture memory files, which could lead to duplicate search results across both the focused `memory-dir-main` collection and the wider `workspace-main` collection. The immediate solution is to remove or rename the `memory-dir` custom path to eliminate the collision creating `memory-dir-main-2`.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Now I have the full picture. Here's exactly what's happening:\n\n**The bug:** OpenClaw has built-in default collections:\n1. `memory-root-main` → `MEMORY.md`\n2. `memory-alt-main` → `memory.md`\n3. `memory-dir-main` → `memory/**/*.md`\n\nYour `openclaw.json` also defines a custom path named `memory-dir` pointing to the same `memory/` folder. When OpenClaw processes it, `memory-dir-main` is already taken by the default, so `ensureUniqueName()` bumps it to `memory-dir-main-2`. But QMD only knows `memory-dir-main` (the default). **Name collision = search fails.**\n\nThe fix: remove the redundant `memory-dir` custom path (defaults already cover it). I'll also clean up the index and re-embed."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_01UgobDJ7Sx9RNSc6Kj6qP4f","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/aiagnet/.openclaw/openclaw.json","offset":1,"limit":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":1228,"cacheRead":43892,"cacheWrite":719,"totalTokens":45840,"cost":{"input":0.000003,"output":0.01842,"cacheRead":0.0131676,"cacheWrite":0.00269625,"total":0.034286849999999994}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":17